g.text: Learning Objectives:​1. How to access and use the Harvard University Library system to enhance work efficiency and​reliability.​2. The benefits of applying the Harvard University Library resources in the workplace as a Staff member​3. An understanding of resources that exist as part of the Harvard University Library system verses what​resources might be available outside of the system to the average individual​AccesstoonlinelibraryresourcesissomethingthatallHarvardemployeeshave,butfewtake​advantageof.Agoodplacetointroducethiswouldbeduringthenewemployeetechnology​orientationwhichtheTechnologyConsultingServicesdepartmentconductseachweek.Asstatedin​thelearningobjectives,itwouldfirstbeimportanttoshowthenewemployeehowtoaccessthe​onlinelibraryresources.Takethemthroughastepbysteptutorialandactuallyshowthemasearchin​AcademicSearchpremiertogetthemstarted.Next,focusonthebenefitsofusingthelibrary​resourcesoverjustasimpleGooglesearch.Itmaytakealittlelongertofindtherightarticleor​resource,butitiscertainlymorereliableandlikelytopleasewhomeverthenewstaffmemberis​reportingto.Infact,forfacultyassistantsitisagreatwaytofindHarvardBusinessReviewarticles​thattheirfacultymembermayhavewritteninordertogaininsightintotheworkofthefaculty​memberstheysupport.Inaddition,havingtheseresourcesavailablemeansthereshouldbeno​excusetohaveincorrectinformationinareportordeliverableforyourboss.Byusingthelibrary​resourcesonecanensurethattheyareusingthebestavailableinformation,aswellasthemost​factual.Lastly,takethenewemployeesthroughthelistofresourcesandexplainthefeatureslike​InterLibraryLoanwhichwillallowthemtogainaccesstobooksatalloftheIvyLeaguelibraries.​AdditionallygothroughAcademicSearchPremier,theHarvardscholarlyworksrepository,andhow​theseparationofschoolsworkswiththelibraries(essentiallyexplainingthateventhoughthework​fortheBusinessSchooltheyhaveaccesstothelibrariesatallschools).​Thiswouldprovideagoodsummaryandsimplymakethenewemployeesawareofaresource​thatmanystaffdonottakeadvantageof.Inadditiontobeingagoodsourceofreliableandaccurate​information,itcouldgivenewemployeesasecrettiporleguponstaffwhohavealreadybeen​workingatHarvardbutforgottenaboutthelibraryresources.Obviouslyifthereweremoretimeit​wouldbenicetocovermoredetailslikewhateachdatabasecando,howtheGoogleBookssearch​works,andsomegoodsearchtips,butwiththelimitedtime,thislessoncoversthemostimportant​parts.Itwouldalsobehelpfultohaveahandoutofsomekind,orquickreferenceguideforthe​librariesthatthenewemployeecouldtakewiththem.Itwouldhavelinkstothelibrarysites,​explanationsofthedatabases,informationonInterLibraryLoan,libraryhours,etc.Itwouldbeagood​resourceasthenewemployeestartssothattheycankeepitclosetotheirdeskandreferenceit​easilywhennecessary.
